  "prompt": "How do I report fake app on Appstore?",
  "response": "If you encounter a fake app on the App Store, you can report it by following these steps:\n\n1. **Open the App Store**: Launch the App Store app on your device.\n\n2. **Find the App**: Search for the app you want to report.\n\n3. **Scroll Down**: Once you open the app's page, scroll down to find the \u201cRatings & Reviews\u201d section.\n\n4. **Report a Problem**: Look for the option that says \u201cReport a Problem\u201d or \u201cReport\u201d and click on it.\n\n5. **Select Reason**: Choose a reason for your report. You may need to select options such as \"Fake or Scam\" or \"Inappropriate Content.\"\n\n6. **Provide Details**: If prompted, provide any additional details that may help in reviewing the app.\n\n7. **Submit**: After filling out the necessary information, submit your report.\n\nAdditionally, you can also report it through Apple's website:\n\n1. **Visit the Apple Support Page**: Go to the Apple Support page's \"Report a Problem\" section.\n\n2. **Sign In**: You may need to sign in with your Apple ID.\n\n3. **Find the App**: Look for the app you want to report in your purchase history.\n\n4. **Report**: Select the app and follow the instructions to report it.\n\nIf you believe the app is significantly harmful or deceptive, you can also notify Apple through their official support channels or contact them directly. Remember to provide as much information as possible to help in resolving the issue.",
